        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-15 17:21:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> > (1 comment)\n> \n> Thank you!\n\nJorge, another point -- Custom Query is not a simple GET query, meaning the first GET request won't give you back a custom query response. It is intact a two stage query, the first GET request only gives you back a URL, which is then used and modified to create the next PUT request which eventually returns a CqResponse. All this logic is handled in the AaiManager. So a direct Restful GET call to the AaiSimulator will only get you back a URL, and the StandardCoder.decode function may not work correctly. That is why I wanted to understand in a bit more detail what is this test really testing?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "f7644933a474b3a055a8791c521f2a7ab5ecb4c7",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-15 17:34:35.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> > Patch Set 2:\n > >\n > > > (1 comment)\n > >\n > > Thank you!\n > \n > Jorge, another point -- Custom Query is not a simple GET query,\n > meaning the first GET request won't give you back a custom query\n > response. It is intact a two stage query, the first GET request\n > only gives you back a URL, which is then used and modified to\n > create the next PUT request which eventually returns a CqResponse.\n > All this logic is handled in the AaiManager. So a direct Restful\n > GET call to the AaiSimulator will only get you back a URL, and the\n > StandardCoder.decode function may not work correctly. That is why I\n > wanted to understand in a bit more detail what is this test really\n > testing?\n\nI think I got you now, may be you could just remove the standardcoder line and enable the case for now, so you would just test for the 200 OK, does that make things easier?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
